          <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-dec-2024-11-desi-bouterse" target="_blank">Desi Bouterse</a>, the former president of Suriname, died at 79. He was known for his charismatic leadership and populist policies, as well as his involvement in criminal activities. In 2019, he was convicted for the <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-dec-2024-11a-1982-killings" target="_blank">1982 killings</a> and was sentenced to 20 years at the end of the year, but he fled the country and never served time. His political influence involved a <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-dec-2024-11b-1980-coup" target="_blank">1980 coup</a> and leadership until 2020. Bouterse was also convicted in absentia for drug trafficking by a Dutch court. His death has elicited mixed reactions, with supporters mourning him and opponents criticizing his violent legacy.</p>
