          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;"><strong>🇸🇰 Slovakia:</strong>   
          A <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-30-dec-2024-12-diplomatic-dispute" target="_blank">diplomatic dispute</a> between Slovakia and Ukraine has escalated as Slovak Prime Minister Robert Fico threatened to cut electricity supplies to Ukraine in response to Kyiv’s decision to end Russian gas transit via Ukrainian pipelines. Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy announced that the current transit deal with Gazprom, expiring December 31, would not be renewed, accusing Fico of enabling Russia’s war by purchasing its gas. Fico recently met with Russian President Vladimir Putin and criticized Zelenskyy for prioritizing Ukraine’s needs over Slovakia’s energy security. </p>
